## Active Feature: Spec 01 — Cadastro de Entidades (Tenants)

**Plan**: `specs/001-tenant-entities/plan.md`
**Spec**: `specs/001-tenant-entities/spec.md`
**Branch**: `001-tenant-entities`

### Stack
- **API**: Node.js + TypeScript + Fastify 5 + Prisma 7 + Zod + PostgreSQL 16
- **Frontend**: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 8 + Tailwind CSS 4 + React Router 7
- **Design**: `frontend/DESIGN.md` (tokens → CSS variables)

### Architecture
- Monorepo: `api/` (backend) + `frontend/` (UI)
- Platform layer: `/platform/*` (UI), `/api/platform/v1/*` (API)
- Tenant layer (Spec 02): `/t/{slug}/*`, `/api/tenant/v1/*`
- Multi-tenancy: shared DB, `Entity` as tenant root, future tables scoped by `entityId`
- Auth: JWT with `scope: platform` | `scope: tenant` (separate tokens)

### Key paths
- Plan & artifacts: `specs/001-tenant-entities/`
- OpenAPI: `specs/001-tenant-entities/contracts/platform-api.openapi.yaml`
- Data model: `specs/001-tenant-entities/data-model.md`
- Quickstart: `specs/001-tenant-entities/quickstart.md`
- Constitution: `.specify/memory/constitution.md`

### Commands
```powershell
cd docker && docker compose up -d
cd api && npm run dev          # :3000
cd frontend && npm run dev     # :5173
```

### Rules
- Business logic ONLY in `api/` — never in React
- Entity slug immutable after creation; no physical delete
- Platform operators manage entities only — no tenant operational access
- Audit all entity CRUD and auth events
